<br>
I was meaning that in other places of the world there's dictators that oppress their people, and lots of other countries possess chemical/biological/nuclear weapons yet we don't invade them.  Any country that has weapons of that magnitude in their arsenal is a threat (granted some threats are greater, but generally speaking).<br>
<br>
Ever since the Carter Doctrine we made it crystal clear any threat to our vital interests in the middle east would be met with force if needed.  It just seems to me this recent action by the Bush administration took advantage of an idle (yet not insignificant) situation in the middle east, but with a primarily economic objective.  I think the main goal of this war--moreover just our presence in the region the last few decades--is to secure American dominance in the world economy for some time to come, but it also has other humanitarian and world security issues that need to be taken care of anyway.  <br>
<br>
Could the humanitarian issues and disarmament of Iraq been addressed by diplomacy given more time and sustained pressure by the US military?  Perhaps, we'll never know.  However, without a military takeover of Iraq the US wouldn't achieve the desired effect of having a strong say in Iraq's oil industry and subsequent influence over a new, American approved, regime.<br>
<br>
I would support this war on humanitarian issues alone, but everything else is just icing on the cake, regardless of the Bush administrations primary motives, which will be left to discuss for a while yet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rathic>Rathic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/03 8:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> bleh</span><hr size=1> badly formed... u know what i meant :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raiynominouscloud>Raiyn Ominouscloud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/03 9:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lowfyr</span><hr size=1>   I've never listened to Rush Limbaugh and its YOU that doesn't know dick about the media.  Nice comeback by the way , usually your posts are semi decent, but just telling me to shut up and that I don't know dick is pretty sad.  Try again. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
